---
title: Toggle Switch
---
p.-text Toggle switches are used to switch between two possible states.

h3 Examples
p.-text
  | To render a toggle switch, apply the classes <code>a-input</code> and <code>-toggle</code> to an <code>input type="checkbox"</code>.
  | For proper styling, toggle switches require an empty label element defined immediately after their declaration.

h4 Base
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .m-formGroup
      input(type="checkbox", class="a-input -toggle", id="toggle1")
      label(for="toggle1")
  :code(lang="html")
    <input type="checkbox" class="a-input -toggle" id="toggle1">
    <label for="toggle1"></label>

h4 Disabled
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .m-formGroup
      input(type="checkbox", class="a-input -toggle", id="toggle2", disabled)
      label(for="toggle2")
  :code(lang="html")
    <input type="checkbox" class="a-input -toggle" id="toggle2" disabled>
    <label for="toggle2"></label>

h4 No Label
p.-text
  | By default, toggle switches are labeled with text <code>ON/OFF</code>. To disable this, apply the modifier <code>-noText</code>.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .m-formGroup
      input(type="checkbox", class="a-input -toggle -noText", id="toggle3")
      label(for="toggle3")
  :code(lang="html")
    <input type="checkbox" class="a-input -toggle -noText" id="toggle3">
    <label for="toggle3"></label>

h4 Stacked
p.-text
  | Group toggle switches in <code>m-formGroup</code> for easy stacking.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .m-formGroup.-mb2
      input(type="checkbox", class="a-input -toggle -noText", id="toggle4")
      label(class="-mr1", for="toggle4")
      span.-text Notifications
    .m-formGroup
      input(type="checkbox", class="a-input -toggle -noText", id="toggle5")
      label(class="-mr1", for="toggle5")
      span.-text Outage Alerts
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-formGroup -mb2">
      <input type="checkbox" class="a-input -toggle -noText" id="toggle4">
      <label for="toggle4"></label>
      <span class="-text">Notifications</span>
    </div>
    <div class="m-formGroup">
      <input type="checkbox" class="a-input -toggle -noText" id="toggle5">
      <label for="toggle5"></label>
      <span class="-text">Outage Alerts</span>
    </div>

h4 Inline
p.-text
  | Apply the class <code>-inline</code> to <code>m-formGroup</code> to display toggle switches inline.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .m-formGroup.-inline.-mr3
      input(type="checkbox", class="a-input -toggle -noText", id="toggle6")
      label(class="-mr1", for="toggle6")
      span.-text Notifications
    .m-formGroup.-inline
      input(type="checkbox", class="a-input -toggle -noText", id="toggle7")
      label(class="-mr1", for="toggle7")
      span.-text Outage Alerts
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-formGroup -inline -mr3">
      <input type="checkbox" class="a-input -toggle -noText" id="toggle6">
      <label class="-mr1" for="toggle6"></label>
      <span class="-text">Notifications</span>
    </div>
    <div class="m-formGroup -inline">
      <input type="checkbox" class="a-input -toggle -noText" id="toggle7">
      <label class="-mr1" for="toggle7"></label>
      <span class="-text">Outage Alerts</span>
    </div>
